    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Christian holiday celebrating the birth of St. John the Baptist, held on June 24. It may include festivities, lights, and fireworks, reminiscent of the earlier feasts of Midsummers for the summer solstice, which occurs at around the same time (on a day between June 21 and 24).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
